<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80b3a14c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s3105"><num value="3105">§ 3105.</num><heading> Buildings not to be draped in mourning</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No building owned, or used for public purposes, by the Federal Government shall be draped in mourning nor may public money be used for that purpose.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80b3a14d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1143">116 Stat. 1143</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
